   "source": [
    "# Define X and Y variables\n",
    "X = df.drop(\"Outcome\", axis = 1) # All the columns except Outcome as it is target(Y) variable, axis = 1 - for column selection\n",
    "Y = df['Outcome']\n",
    "\n",
    "# Train test split\n",
    "X_train, X_test, Y_train, Y_test = train_test_split(X, Y, test_size = 0.2, random_state = 25)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Logistic Regression Model - predicts probability and converts it to class either 0 or 1\n",
    "\n",
    "#Create the model\n",
    "model = LogisticRegression()\n",
    "\n",
    "#Train the model using X train & Y_train\n",
    "model.fit(X_train, Y_train)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Model Predictions done on X_test\n",
    "Y_pred = model.predict(X_test)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Probability Predicitions (ROC requirement)\n",
    "# To predict the probabilities after using logit function where the probab. ranges from 0 to 1\n",
    "# 1st column is 1-yprob, yprob, we need second column so we use [:, 1:]\n",
    "Y_prob = model.predict_proba(X_test)[:,1:]"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "032441ba-ac1e-44a6-a19d-93af99114bcd",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# 4. Model Evaluation:\n",
    "- Evaluate the performance of the model on the testing data using accuracy, precision, recall, F1-score, and ROC-AUC score.\n",
    "- Visualize the ROC curve."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 12,
   "id": "dd2f2633-38e3-40d9-bfec-9b3a21553fc5",
